<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>    <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Name another spell in the game that, if removed, would essentially break EQ.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Spells are akin to abilities.  Take defensive away from warriors, fd away from monks and sk's, and EQ is broken.<br>
<br>
Cheal is a single spell, but it is akin to its own spell line.  At level 39, cheal is only going to be healing 800hp or so, in VT it's going to heal for 1-5K.  It's not really a 10K heal, in terms of practical use. If you look at it as its own spell line, I can think of a lot of lines that, if removed, would certainly break EQ -- mez and slow for instance.<br>
<br>
Items and spells are akin to equipment.  Take haste items out of EQ, the game is broken.  You can go on and on with this line of thought.<br>
