Ok, although my 1600hp at level 39 is assuming a somewhat twinked warrior's max hp, the average CH on a 39 warrior would be 800 to 1000 if you are playing safe. Your VT example is based on a CH chain healing 1000 if few hits land, to 5000 at worse case (any more and the MT is dead). But in an XP group, at full main assist health, the cleric can basically go /afk, take a smoke, get a drink, etc., come back and use 400 mana to recover 6000hps. At level 60, with top gear, that's maybe 10, 15 percent of the cleric's total mana to heal 80 to 90 percent of the warriors health.<br>
<br>
FD is another ability/spell that's flawed, but if it was removed, it would take much less effort retuning the game than if CH was removed. Defensive, probably easier seeing as it's used mostly on high-end encounters, much less to adjust.<br>
<br>
What I'd like to see is a replacement to CH at level 39 that has a similar cast time and mana cost, but heal a max of 1600hps. Then at level 49, an upgrade with a slightly higher cost, same cast time, but heal for 2400 or so. Then at level 59 you get a modified Complete, with the 10 second cast, but a variable cost based on the level of the person healed, maybe level * 10, minimum 400).<br>
