<br>
Cheal isn't more broken or out of whack than the rest of the game at this point.  <br>
<br>
And no, I don't see anything wrong with a self balancing spell.  It's the same as having (generally):<br>
<br>
39 cheal 1 400 800<br>
49 cheal 2 400 1200<br>
55 cheal 3 400 2000<br>
60 cheal 4 400 3000<br>
ancient cheal 400 5000<br>
<br>
Yes, the mana stays the same, but it's the ratio that's important anyway.  I don't think that those ratios are totally out of whack for a spell with a 10 second casting time for a class that is specialized. [edit: especilly when cheal isn't helped by casting time mod items]<br>
<br>
You asked if the removal of any other spell can break the game, and I countered with other abilities that, with their removal, would break the game just as much.  You couldn't do high end encounters without defensive, for instance.  Sure, you could rebalance the game to compensate, and you could do the same for cheal, if the need was there, but it's not, not without a complete game redesign.<br>
<br>
